== German ==

=== Etymology ===

Unclear; possibly originated as a rhyme for [[Lorke]], as a combination of ''[[knorrig]]'' "strong, robust" and the Low German diminutive suffix ''-ke'', or from the play "''Die Familie Knorke''" by [[w:Rudolf Melzer|Rudolf Melzer]].

=== Adjective ===

'''knorke'''

# {{informal}} [[great]], [[very good]]

=== Usage notes ===

Primarily used in [[w:Berlin|Berlin]] and the [[w:Ruhr|Ruhr]] basin; typically understood (but not used) in other parts of Germany.

=== Example ===

* "''Knorke ist dreimal so [[schnafte]] wie [[dufte]].''"

